movie:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "Bluehills is now home to something claiming to be a 'movie' theatre. Modern nonsense?"
        "[Check out the modern nonsense] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            run transition_black cinema
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map

    set data.global.visitedMovieTheater true
    "The theatre! All the glitz and glamour one would expect of the burgeoning 'movie' industry packed into a single grim building that looks as though it hasn't been repaired in fifty years, despite only being hurriedly built overtop of some rubble just over a year ago."
    "The facade is plastered in posters for upcoming 'movies', each promising you an even more enchanting and astounding time than the last."
    clear_dialog
    "The lady in the ticket booth eyes you sleepily. She yawns."
    if (roll movie_oogler_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "She can already tell you're an oogler, not a buyer. She's only had this job for a month, but already it's instinct."
        talk orb talk "She realises that she has started subconsciously sorting strangers into 'customer' and 'background character', and fears how her psyche will be mangled and changed by this job."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Ohoho! Darlings, if you think about it, we're all 'movies'! Because we *move* around! Yes? Don't you think? Tee hee!"
    talk nasty talk "Shut the fuck up you dumb broad."
    talk orb talk "Agreed. Shut the fuck up, Lovely Lady."
    jump movie_menu

movie_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The wall to the side of the theatre is decorated with posters for the meagre selection of films currently being shown."
        "[Look at the poster for the 'movie' <span class='writtenText'>'Unedited Footage of a Teatime'</span>]":
            jump movie_teatime
        "[Look at the poster for the 'movie' <span class='writtenText'>'The Unshot Bullet Murders'</span>]":
            jump movie_murder
        "[Look at the poster for the 'movie', wait, there isn't a poster here, it's just an empty frame!]":
            jump movie_blank
        "[Look at the poster for the 'movie' <span class='writtenText'>'Train Rushes Towards Camera: You Won't Believe What Doesn't Happen Next!'</span>]"
            jump movie_train
        "[Look at the poster for the 'movie' <span class='writtenText'>'Wuppets Go To War'</span>]":
            jump movie_wuppets
        "[Stop looking at posters and do something else with your day] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            jump goToGameMap

movie_teatime:
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "Looks shit, right?"
        "Extremely.":
            talk lovely talk "Tsk tsk. You two wouldn't know good storytelling if it hit you in the face."
            clear_dialog
            talk poppy talk "I know I don't."
        "I think it looks good. I love watching little ladies sip their teas and nibble their cakes for hours and hours without ever finishing them.":
            talk nasty talk "Pervert."
    jump movie_menu

movie_murder:
    talk nasty talk "It's about a serial killer who kills their victims by manually stabbing them to death with a bullet. It's great. Bopper shit. Based on a true story too."
    if (roll movie_murder_real_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "It absolutely is *not* based on a true story." 
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog  
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Sounds ghastly. It's precisely this sort of filth that will cement moving pictures as naught but a passing fad."
        "Agreed, it's disgusting. [Shake your head disapprovingly]":
            talk lovely talk "Mhm. Personally, I support the implementation of the 'lovely code' to ensure this sort of filth stays off our... whatever 'movies' get shown on. Big book pages? Photo frames?"
        "That sounds like it bops. I love ghastly movies.":
            talk lovely talk "Tsk. You two are simply awful."
    jump movie_menu

movie_blank:
    "It's a blank poster frame. A poster should be here, but it isn't."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Riveting. Can we look at something else now?"
        "No. [Keep looking at the empty poster frame]":
            clear_dialog
            wait 4000
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Good good. Let's get g- wait, did you say no? *Why*?"
                "It might get interesting.":
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "It really wont."
                        "[Keep looking at the empty poster frame]":
                            clear_dialog
                            wait 8000
                            "A small, torn up bit of paper, the corner of a now removed poster, is still attached to the top left corner of the frame. It is yellowing, and dry as burnt paper."
                            "It feels wrong, this lack of poster. Yes, this isn't just an empty poster frame, it's something more."
                            if (roll movie_blank_poster_nightmare nightmare 40):
                                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>it's you, isn't it?</span>"
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                            clear_dialog
                            talk nasty talk "Boooooored."
                            talk lovely talk "Mhm. I do have to concur with my compagnes. For want of a better word staring at this poster is... well, 'Tis rather dull, don't you think? Might we quit this place, post-haste?"
                            talk nasty talk "Lovely Lady, I am fucking begging you to stop using entire paragraphs where one word will suffice."
                            talk lovely talk "Goodness Nasty Girl, that was an awful lot of words for such a monosyllabic mammal. Tell me darling, did you not mean simply to say 'sut'?"
                            talk nasty talk "Sut..."
                        "[Stop staring at the empty poster frame]":
                            talk orb talk "Thank you."
                "I'm just messing with you, sorry. [Stop staring at the empty poster frame]":
                    talk orb talk "Whatever. Let's stop now."
        "Okay. [Stop staring at the empty poster frame]":
            talk orb talk "Thank you."
    jump movie_menu

movie_train:
    choice:
        "You look at the poster, and realise with horror that it depicts a train PLOUGHING DIRECTLY TOWARDS YOU!"
        roll movie_train_roll_nasty nasty 80 "[Attempt to dodge roll out of the way]":
            success "":
                "You artfully fling yourself out of harms way, and land in a shit-hot pose a few meters away from the danger zone."
                clear_dialog
                "The air is tense. How close was your doom?"
                clear_dialog
                wait 4000
                "The train must have put the brakes on."
            failure "":
                play sound punch
                run transition_pain
                "You fling yourself out of harms way, directly into the road, where you bounce off of the bonnet of an automobile."
                clear_dialog
                "You land in a crumpled heap, looking battered, but basically feeling also battered. Fortunately, the scene does not branch too wildly, as the driver is speeding out of here instead of stopping to check you're ok."
                if (roll movie_train_robbery_orb orb 40):
                    talk orb talk "They're smuggling stolen goods. Last thing they want is to stop here, have the police turn up and get sent to the slammer for stealing five crates of hammers."
                else:
                    wait 1000
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk nasty talk "You okay there Ghost, I've hit a couple of cunts with my automobile before and they're usually pretty badly hurt."
                    "[Climb back to your feet and stretch your muscles] I think this actually made me feel better. Kind of like a high velocity massage.":
                        choice:
                            talk nasty talk "Fucken ace."
                            "Let's not celebrate too soon! That train could be here any moment! [Prepare to do another dodge roll]":
                                run skip
        "[Close your eyes and brace for death]":
            set data.movie.braced true
            run transition generic_black
            "You close your eyes. Slow your breathing. This is it. You had a good run..."
            clear_dialog
            wait 8000
            choice:
                "Nothing appears to be happening."
                "[Open your eyes]":
                    "The train appears to have put the brakes on."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "It's a photograph, Ghost. It can't hurt you."
        "Oh.":
            if $data.movie.braced:
                run transition cinema
            choice:
                "Orb is right. The train has not moved."
                "[Slick back your hair] Bopper. I knew that. I was only pretending. [Turn to the lady in the booth] \\"I WAS DOING A BIT, I DIDN'T ACTUALLY GET SCARED! IF ANYONE ASKS IF I WAS SCARED TELL THEM I WASN'T!\\"":
                    talk nasty talk "She thinks you're so cool now. You're so smooth, Ghost."
                    if (roll movie_train_shift_orb orb 40):
                        talk orb talk "You're the third person to make that mistake this shift. She barely even registered it."
                "We were safe this time, but let's not test our luck by attending the actual screening.":
                    talk orb talk "Mhm. Sure. That's where the real danger lies."    
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Is it safe to open our eyes yet!? I'm so scared! Squeak squeak!"
    jump movie_menu

movie_wuppets:
    set data.ghost.sawWuppets true
    "In this fun, musical family adventure, The fuzzy, goofy Wuppets swallow their iodine tablets, fix their bayonets, and get shredded by machine gun fire breaking through the Iron Curtain in their quest to raise the Red Ram over St.Petrogradsburg. Guest starring Anglia's #1 Badminton sensation, Judy Baps."
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Why are you showing me these revolting demons from the underworld! Eugh! Disgusting!"
    talk nasty talk "Oi, don't you shit-talk The Wuppets. They're a proper bunch of lads."
    talk nasty talk "Besides, Ms Baps is in this one, and she sweats like a.. well, like a badminton player, don't she?"
    jump movie_menu